{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f76985ee-ab9d-4046-ba73-9fcdc869d752","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\n**Then:**\n- Install the .NET 11 SDK locally.\n- Run `dotnet restore` to pick up updated packages.\n- Update any `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*` or `Microsoft.Extensions.*` NuGet packages to their 11.x versions.\n- Build and test: `dotnet build && dotnet test`.\n\nCheck the [.NET 11 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/) for any breaking changes relevant to your app.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e430a08c-b0d3-4c9e-8cc9-cb031026c081","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question I can answer from knowledge — no need to search their codebase since they've already told me what needs to change.","outputTokens":333,"requestId":"142E:28BCD7:E06AE4E:FA0F762:69EC1B71"},"id":"eee23ba8-3658-4368-8e07-cdfc8be03155","timestamp":"2026-04-25T01:40:08.690Z","parentId":"35bd673c-a4ab-494a-8c07-ca231cfd54e5"}
